[***Problem 3. What does the `distinct` function do?***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

Your answer should refer to \[https://r4ds.hadley.nz/data-transform.html#distinct\\\](https://r4ds.hadley.nz/data-transform.html#distinct){.uri} and what is demonstrated in the following code and the `HallOfFame` dataset.

The distinct function will, "find all the unique rows in a dataset, so technically, it primarily operates on the rows." In my own words, this function will select the unique or recognizably different outputs from each row, although it can be used on columns by supplying column names.

In this context, it is finding the ten most distinct or outstanding players, in a good way that is rather than the bottom ten, and compiling them into a list. Theoretically, this would provide us with a top ten list of the greatest baseball players of all time through qualitative data.

```{r}
HallOfFame |>
  arrange(playerID) |>
  head(10)

HallOfFame |>
  distinct(playerID) |>
  arrange(playerID) |>
  head(10)

HallOfFame |>
  distinct(playerID, .keep_all = TRUE) |>
  arrange(playerID) |>
  head(10)
```

